article.headline: New Mexico State 60, Boise State 59
article.story:
RENO, Nev. (AP) -- Jenean Ford hit a layup with 22 seconds left
to help New Mexico State beat Boise State 60-59 Friday in the
semifinals of the Western Athletic Conference tournament.

Jessica Thompson missed the second of two free throws for the
sixth-seeded Broncos (15-15) with 5.1 seconds left that could have
tied the score.

Monique Bribiescas scored 23 points to lead the seventh-seeded
Aggies (10-19), who advance to Saturday's championship game against
the winner of the Nevada-Louisiana Tech game.

Ford added 16 points for New Mexico State, which used a 13-3 run
midway through the second half to build a 50-42 lead with 8:24 to
play.

Boise State responded with a 9-2 run to pull to within a point
at 52-51 with 5:33 left. The Broncos tied the score at 58 with 51
seconds left on a 3-pointer by Rebecca Kepilino, setting the stage
for Ford's winning basket.

Jackie Lee led Boise State with 13 points. Michelle Hessing
added 10.

The Broncos grabbed a 29-28 lead at halftime, going ahead on
Thompson's 15-foot jumper with 5 seconds left. It was the first
time the Broncos had led since 3-0 on Jackie Lee's 3-pointer to
open the scoring in the game.
